-- MOVES-Jersey Finance hires 2 executives to boost Greater China presence
-- 
-- Tue Oct 07, 2014 12:22PM EDT
-- None



Oct 7 (Reuters) - International finance company Jersey Finance said it appointed Yumei Zhang director of business development in its Hong Kong office to increase its presence in the Greater China region.

Jersey Finance also appointed Garry Zhao project manager in the Shanghai office to maximize growth opportunities in mainland China, the company said in a statement. Zhang joins Jersey Finance from Louvre Group, where she most recently headed the Hong Kong office.